", "proof": ["  have h1 : ∀ y : ℝ, deriv p y * deriv q y = 98 := hf'
  have h2 : ∀ y : ℝ, deriv q y ≠ 0 := fun y => by
    intro h3
    have h4 : deriv p y * deriv q y = 98 := h1 y
    rw [h3] at h4
    norm_num at h4
  have h3 : ∀ y : ℝ, deriv p y > 0 := hP
  have h4 : ∀ y : ℝ, deriv q y > 0 := fun y => by
    have h5 : deriv p y * deriv q y = 98 := h1 y
    have h6 : deriv p y > 0 := h3 y
    have h7 : deriv q y ≠ 0 := h2 y
    linarith
  have h5 : p 0 = q 0 ∧ q 0 > 0 := h0
  have h6 : p x + 2 * q x > 28 * x := by
    have h7 : x ∈ Icc (0: ℝ) (1: ℝ) := hD
    have h8 : 0 ≤ x ∧ x ≤ 1 := h7
    have h9 : deriv p x > 0 := h3 x
    have h10 : deriv q x > 0 := h4 x
    have h11 : deriv p 0 > 0 := h3 0
    have h12 : deriv q 0 > 0 := h4 0
    have h13 : p 0 = q 0 := h5.1
    have h14 : q 0 > 0 := h5.2

      have h16 : ∃ u : ℝ, u ∈ Ioo 0 x ∧ deriv p u = (p x - p 0) / x := by
        apply exists_deriv_eq_slope
        exact hpDeriv
        exact h8.1
        exact h8.2
      have h17 : ∃ u : ℝ, u ∈ Ioo 0 x ∧ deriv q u = (q x - q 0) / x := by
        apply exists_deriv_eq_slope
        exact hqDeriv
        exact h8.1
        exact h8.2
      obtain ⟨u1, h18, h19⟩ := h16
      obtain ⟨u2, h20, h21⟩ := h17
      have h22 : deriv p u1 = (p x - p 0) / x := h19
      have h23 : deriv q u2 = (q x - q 0) / x := h21
      have h24 : deriv p u1 * deriv q u2 = 98 := h1 y
      have h25 : (p x - p 0) / x * (q x - q 0) / x = 98 := by
        rw [h22, h23] at h24
        exact h24
      have h26 : (p x - p 0) * (q x - q 0) = 98 * x ^ 2 := by
        field_simp at h25
        ring_nf at h25
        exact h25
      have h27 : p x - p 0 > 0 := by
        have h28 : deriv p u1 > 0 := h9
        have h29 : u1 ∈ Ioo 0 x := h18
        have h30 : 0 < u1 ∧ u1 < x := h29
        have h31 : p 0 < p u1 := by
          apply lt_of_deriv_pos
          exact hpDeriv
          exact h30.1
          exact h30.2
        linarith
      have h28 : q x - q 0 > 0 := by
        have h29 : deriv q u2 > 0 := h10
        have h30 : u2 ∈ Ioo 0 x := h20
        have h31 : 0 < u2 ∧ u2 < x := h30
        have h32 : q 0 < q u2 := by
          apply lt_of_deriv_pos
          exact hqDeriv
          exact h31.1
          exact h31.2
        linarith
      have h29 : p x + 2 * q x > 28 * x := by
        have h30 : p x > 28 * x - 2 * q 0 := by
          linarith

{"name": "ln463", "problem": "example (x: ℝ) (p q : ℝ → ℝ) (h0 : p 0 = q 0 ∧ q 0 > 0) (hf': ∀ y:ℝ, (deriv p y) * (deriv q y) = 75) (hqDeriv: Differentiable ℝ q) (hpDeriv: Differentiable ℝ p) (hP: ∀ y:ℝ, deriv p y > 0) (hD: x ∈ Icc (0: ℝ) (1: ℝ)): p x + 3 * q x > 30 * x := by
", "proof": ["  obtain ⟨h0, h1⟩ := h0
  have h2 : 0 < q 0 := h1
  have h3 : ∀ y:ℝ, 0 < deriv p y := hP
  have h4 : ∀ y:ℝ, deriv p y * deriv q y = 75 := hf'
  have h5 : Differentiable ℝ q := hqDeriv
  have h6 : Differentiable ℝ p := hpDeriv
  -- Apply the Mean Value Theorem to q on the interval [0, x]
  have h7 : ∀ y ∈ Icc (0: ℝ) x, 0 < deriv q y := by
    intro y hy
    have h8 : 0 < deriv p y := h3 y
    have h9 : deriv p y * deriv q y = 75 := h4 y
    exact lt_of_le_of_lt (mul_nonneg (deriv_nonneg_of_nonneg (fun z => le_of_lt (h3 z)) y) (deriv_nonneg_of_nonneg (fun z => le_of_lt (h3 z)) y)) h9
  have h10 : ∀ y ∈ Icc (0: ℝ) x, 0 < deriv q y := h7
  have h11 : 0 < deriv q x := h10 x ⟨le_refl 0, le_refl x⟩
  -- Apply the Mean Value Theorem to p on the interval [0, x]
  have h12 : ∀ y ∈ Icc (0: ℝ) x, 0 < deriv p y := h3
  have h13 : 0 < deriv p x := h12 x ⟨le_refl 0, le_refl x⟩
  -- Use the fact that p(0) = q(0) and q(0) > 0 to show that p(x) + 3q(x) > 30x
  have h14 : p x + 3 * q x > 30 * x := by
    have h15 : p x + 3 * q x > p 0 + 3 * q 0 := by
      have h16 : p x > p 0 := by
        apply lt_of_le_of_lt (deriv_nonneg_of_nonneg (fun z => le_of_lt (h3 z)) x) h13
      have h17 : q x > q 0 := by
        apply lt_of_le_of_lt (deriv_nonneg_of_nonneg (fun z => le_of_lt (h3 z)) x) h11
      linarith
    linarith
  exact h14
```"], "complete": true, "out": [], "informal_hints": ""}
